The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, May 24, 2004 				 Ciant eyes sales pact with Webel
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, May 23: The US-based Ciant Technologies is in talks with nodal agency Webel to distribute its data quality management products.																								Ciant Corporation chairman and CEO Anirudha Basu said, We have developed an India-centric strategy in the last seven months and plan to enter into partnerships to market our products.																								The company has a research and development (R amp;D) unit in the city for over five years and plans to expand its operations to include a data centre. The R amp;D centre will develop products for the global and domestic markets.																								It is also scouting for other locations in the country to set up a data centre.																								Ciant prefers to focus on developing new products. It already has partnerships with IBM, PricewaterhouseCoopers and Unisys among others for the distribution of its products.																								Ciant will introduce data quality tools to enhance homeland security, fraud management and best practices in customer relationship management (CRM).																								Our target clients are organisations in the finance, telecom, retail, publishing and government sectors, where a huge amount of data is generated and open to fraud, said Basu. 
